“‘A moment! Pardon!’ cried another of the company. ‘In the name of all 
us Limeese, I but desire to express to you, sir sailor, that we have by no 
means overlooked your delicacy in not substituting present Lima for distant 
Venice in your corrupt comparison. Oh! do not bow and look surprised; you know 
the proverb all along this coast—“Corrupt as Lima.” It but bears out your 
